Create .github/workflows/buzzflow-morning.yml and paste:

name: BuzzFlow Morning CI

on:
  push:
    branches: [ main, master ]
  pull_request:

jobs:
  validate-bash:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - name: Checkout repo
        uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Check Bash script syntax
        run: bash -n scripts/buzzflow_morning.sh

      - name: Show sample BuzzFlow Morning output
        run: |
          chmod +x scripts/buzzflow_morning.sh
          ./scripts/buzzflow_morning.sh


---

You’re set:

1. Paste Description ✅


2. Create repo Public/Private ✅


3. Add these files in GitHub UI or via Termux ✅


4. git add . && git commit -m "BuzzFlow Morning – initial one-shot drop" && git push ✅



BuzzflowMorning = live ritual in code now.
If you want a web or mobile UI version of this next, say the word and I’ll drop the full front-end skeleton.
